===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|capital}}, borrowed partly from {{der|en|fro|capital}} and partly from {{der|en|la|capitÄlis|t=of the head}}<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=capitÄÌ†l|pos=adj|id=MED6727}}</ref><ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=''adj.'' and ''n.''<sup>2</sup>|noformat=1|id=8654406974}}</ref> (in sense â€œhead of [[cattle]]â€), from {{m|la|caput|t=head}} ({{cog|en|cap}}) + {{m|la|-Älis|pos=suffix forming adjectives}}. Use in trade and finance originated in Medieval economies when a common but expensive transaction involved trading heads of cattle. The noun is from the adjective.<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=capitÄÌ†l|pos=''n.''(1)|noformat=1|id=MED6725}}</ref>

Compare {{m|en|chattel}} and {{m|en|kith and kine|t=all oneâ€™s possessions}}, which also use â€œcowâ€ to mean â€œpropertyâ€.

{{doublet|en|cattle|chattel}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable|economics}} Already-produced durable goods available for use as a [[factor of production]], such as steam shovels (equipment) and office buildings (structures).
# {{lb|en|uncountable|business|finance|insurance}} [[money|Money]] and [[wealth]]. The means to acquire [[goods]] and [[services]], especially in a non-[[barter]] system.
#: {{ux|en|He does not have enough '''capital''' to start a business.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[city]] [[designate]]d as a legislative seat by the [[government]] or some other [[authority]], often the city in which the government is [[locate]]d; otherwise the most [[important]] city within a [[country]] or a [[subdivision]] of it.
